se:Description.se:Title: Habitat and Biotopes Default Style
se:Description.se:Abstract: Natura2000 habitat types in North Rhine-Westphalia, Germany are presented in maps that have commonly used these styles for the app. 40 habitat types of the Habitat Directive that occur in North Rhine-Westphalia over the past ten years. Thus this style could serve as an EXAMPLE for a style for all habitat types under the Habitat Directive. Point geometries are rendered as circles (6110, 6210, 8160, 8210, 8220, 8230) and a triangle (8310) each with a size of 18 pixels, with a pistachio green (#D7D79E - 6110), dark grass green (#619669 - 6210), light grey (#B2B2B2 - 8160), white (#FFFFFF - 8210), dark grey (#828282 - 8220, 8230), black (#000000 - 8310) fill and a black (#000000) outline except 8220 with a dark green (#00734C) outline 8230 and 8310 without an outline. Line geometries are rendered as a brown (#966E00) line with a stroke width of 1 pixel. Polygon geometries are rendered using a dark blue (#004DA8 - 3110), dark blue (#3753A7 - 3130), dark blue (#004DA8 - 3140), night blue (#002673 - 3160), light fuchsia (#E8BEFF - 4010), purple (#8400A8 - 4030), dark grass green (#619669 - 6210), yellow (#F8EC00 - 6430), light green (#AAFF00 - 6510), night blue (#004DA8 - 6510), dark red (#730000 - 7110), yellow ochre (#E0AA0F - 7120), light limegreen (#ECF593 - 7230), light grey (#E1E1E1 - 8210), dark grey (#686868 - 8230), black (#000000 - 8310), green (#38A800 - 9160), dark pistachio green (#728944 - 9180), green (#009617 - 9190), green (#009617 - 9190) fill and a solid black (#000000 - 9160, 8230, 8210, 7230, 7120, 7110, 6510, 6430, 6210, 4030, 4010, 3160, 3140, 3110) outline with a stroke width of 0,4 pixel and with a stroke of 1 pixel (6510). Following polygons geometries have no outline color: 3130, 8310, 9180, 9190. The following polygon geometries have currently no content: 1340, 2310, 2330, 3150, 3260, 3270, 5130, 6110, 6130, 6230, 6410, ?, 6520, 7140, 7150, 7210, 7220, 8150, 8160, 8220, 9110, 9130, 9150, 9170, 91D0, 91E0 and 91F0.
